cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper discusses a tool for performance modeling of loop kernels, which falls under the category of computer systems and architecture (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the use of analytic loop performance modeling, which could fall under the category of performance analysis (cs.PF). The tool itself is a software engineering tool (cs.SE) that automates the process of constructing performance models. Additionally, the paper discusses stencil performance modeling, which could fall under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
